    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI change the workspace library for lua_ls based on some conditions. For example, if I am inside my neovim config I add `$VIMRUNTIME` and installed plugins.\r\n\r\n`lua-language-server --version`: 3.7.4\r\n\r\nSomehow this does not work as expected anymore.\r\n\r\nI bisected this to [9f8c962](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/9f8c96240dc0318bd92a646966917e8fe0641144)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`lua-language-server` in `$PATH`\r\n\r\n`init.lua`\r\n```lua\r\nlocal group = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup(\"LSP\", { clear = true })\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"FileType\", {\r\n  group = group,\r\n  pattern = \"lua\",\r\n  callback = function(args)\r\n    vim.lsp.start {\r\n      name = \"lua-ls\",\r\n      cmd = { \"lua-language-server\" },\r\n      filetypes = { \"lua\" },\r\n      on_init = function(client)\r\n        client.config.settings = vim.tbl_deep_extend(\"force\", client.config.settings, {\r\n          Lua = {\r\n            workspace = {\r\n              library = {\r\n                vim.env.VIMRUNTIME,\r\n              },\r\n            },\r\n          },\r\n        })\r\n      end,\r\n      settings = {\r\n        Lua = {\r\n          runtime = {\r\n            version = \"LuaJIT\",\r\n          },\r\n        },\r\n      },\r\n    }\r\n  end,\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n`nvim --clean -u init.lua init.lua`\r\nPressing `K` over any `vim` shows `(global) vim: unknown`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPressing `K` over any `vim` shows correct type information\r\n\r\n\r\n## Workaround\r\nIf I change `on_init` function to: (`Lua` key moved outside of `vim.tbl_deep_extend`)\r\n```lua\r\n      on_init = function(client)\r\n        client.config.settings.Lua = vim.tbl_deep_extend(\"force\", client.config.settings.Lua, {\r\n          workspace = {\r\n            library = {\r\n              vim.env.VIMRUNTIME,\r\n            },\r\n          },\r\n        })\r\n      end,\r\n```\r\nThen this works as expected.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0-dev-2514+g5b312cd5f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narch linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.31.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
